Virginia Tech, founded in 1872, dominates life in Blacksburg with a $900 million budget.
The campus was rocked by a gunman's deadly rampage, killing 32 people in dorms and classrooms.
The FBI ruled out terrorism as the cause.
President Bush attended a memorial service, calling it a "day of sadness" for the nation.
The university canceled classes for the week, urging caution and cooperation with the ongoing investigation.
The tragic event, the deadliest school shooting in US history, left the Virginia Tech community and the nation in mourning.
